cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper discusses security issues in wireless mesh networks, which are a type of wireless network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper specifically focuses on secure routing, which suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses vulnerabilities and attacks, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses preventive mechanisms, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
